[[Image:Ampoule.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Pharmaceutical [[ampoule]], a type of vial.]]
A '''vial''' or '''phial''' is a [[glass]] vessel or [[bottle]], especially a small bottle used to store [[medicine]]s.

==Etymology==
The word "vial" comes from the [[Greek]] word ''phiale'' meaning "a broad flat container."

